<br>
You could end up with a connection over time that is equal to 256k DSL and could do nothing more than just disconnect your service.<br>
<br>
Most companies that provide any kind of service always leave a clause in there for themselves, they can at any change cancel the contract and your service, they can also change serveral things that are stipulated within the contract.<br>
<br>
Contracts mean shit for you but alot more for them. <p><TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" and CELLPADING="0" WIDTH="100%">
