<br>
Even rental agreements are subject to the same things. It just depends on how bright the attorney is who draws it all up.<br>
<br>
Basically the reason why they don't promise a certain amount of bandwidth is because depending on your area you could be sharing that connection with more people than say someone who lives in the same complex as old people who would rather pluck out their eyes with forks than use a computer, let alone the internet.<br>
<br>
Your connection could vary from 128k to 1.5MB. Just depends on where you are, wiring in your building and bandwidth saturation.<br>
<br>
I didn't have a cap on my cable either, but AT&amp;T decided they were going to impose a 5GIG per month limit. They sent out a nice letter to everyone and let us know. <br>
<br>
I never hit it myself or if I did they never shutoff my service. Then again at that time I was doing nothing but playing EQ so, who had time for pr0n? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
